reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The XIXILAND Car Seat Toys are an absolute lifesaver for parents of infants. This versatile set caters to babies' development stages, offering engaging toys suitable for ages 0-12 months. The inclusion of a dinosaur, lion mirror, and teether ensures a variety of sensory experiences crucial for brain development. The toys are thoughtfully designed with vibrant colors, different textures, and interactive elements to stimulate curiosity and motor skills. They easily attach to car seats and strollers, providing entertainment and distraction during outings or car rides. With their durable construction and baby-safe materials, these toys provide peace of mind for parents while offering endless entertainment for little ones. Overall, the XIXILAND Car Seat Toys are a must-have addition to any infant's playtime repertoire.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good travel toy for car seat/teething
reviews.reviewText: This car seat toy is excellent for keeping your little munchkin busy in the car seat when facing backwards. I think the variety of colors and textures is very important. Especially for young developing minds. The toy seems safe and sturdy, however I do feel some of the pieces loosened a little easily but not to the point where they would come off. It definitely does its job in terms of keeping my son busy. It seems to secure well to the car seat. Overall build quality is probably a 4 out of 5. I would recommend this at its price point. By the way this traveled well through couple different airports for us.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Adorable and colorful
reviews.reviewText: With my friend and her baby staying with me for a while, I wanted to ensure their comfort and enjoyment, especially during travel. These toys have exceeded my expectations! Not only are they adorable and colorful, but they also provide great stimulation for the baby's developing senses. The soft textures and gentle rattling sounds keep the little one engaged and content, making car rides much more enjoyable for everyone involved.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good toy overall
reviews.reviewText: I ordered this and another (dif designs) one for a boy and one for a girl. They are good quality and bright clear colors. It gets the babies interest. It's very soft. It does what it's supposed to wrapping on the cars seat handle but it's loose and doesn't stretch all the way across. It will work as a toy they can carry around when a little bigger but as far as for newborns and using on the cars seat it's OK. It would be better if it had a way to secure it better. There are straps you can tie but not really long enough unless you want to tie a knot in it. In order to not have it pulled off and fall on the floor and cause you to have to constantly fetch it in the car, I would suggest trying to find a way to attach it somehow with those little shower curtain style rings that are sold for hanging baby toys. But the product itself is very nice and captures their attention. The designs are on all sides so it doesnt matter how it swings. It could be used on the car seat, crib, or just about anywhere, and it seems safe enough to be carried and chewed on by any age baby or Toddler. Even though stretching across would give you more options to posistion it, the payoff is that you can scoot it out of your way while grabbing the handle. Even with the "attaching" issue, I find this a quality toy and so do the babies, I would highly recommend this. I hope this info has been helpful.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars cute, colorful, but funny odor
reviews.reviewText: This car-seat toy is vibrant and so cute with a little stuffed panda at the top followed by a stuffed dinosaur, lion, and then a bird. It will work well as a car seat toy, a shopping cart toy, or even a handheld toy. But directly out of the package, the toy smells unclean--musty and fishy. I'll need to wash it by hand, according to the instructions, and let it air dry before it's safe to let our little one handle it.
